@bolkedebruin Do you think adding this check when the dagbag is being populated is better? That way the invariant of the dagbag being well-formed is maintained, both at the dag level, and at the higher level.

Of course, since the process that refreshes the dags is called way more often than this `descendants()` method, overall there might be a slight perf hit in that approach. Maintaining a "valid" dagbag always however sounds more robust to me.

What do you think?

